page00.content:
Project background

It has long been a challenge for us to efficiently convert the existing traffic into sales. With the rise of refined operations, it becomes particularly important to take advantage of traffic in a more targeted way. After several attempts, we found that manual push helps identify the "right audience" to avoid annoying users and improve push effects.

Project objective

This project aims to help users discover products via targeted recommendation and increase the open rate of push notifications.

In the first stage, it will implement "Products You May Like" through the Official Account.

In the second stage, it will dig deeper into users' browsing behaviors on the Official Account and add "Products You May Like" to the official website.

Requirement overview

The recommendation consists of three modules: user and product profile, trigger and match strategies, and recommendation logic. The details and complete process are as follows:

  1. User and product profile: Dig into the characteristics of users and products to provide data support for the match strategies.
  2. Trigger and match strategies: Identify users/products for recommendation and match the right audience with the right products.
  3. Recommendation logic: Control recommendation channels, recommendation time, and content assembly. The second and third modules support A/B testing, and can be adjusted in real time based on the collected behavioral data.

1 How can I create a space?

Wiki admins can click the quick navigation bar on the left side or the "Create space" button in the "All projects" list to create a space.

Team admins can go to "Team management" > "Team settings" at the upper right corner to configure the list of Wiki admins.

2 How can I configure the space permissions?

Wiki space allows you to configure 3 types of permissions: "View and comment", "Create/edit/delete/share", and "Manage project" for your spaces.

Wiki admins can configure the list of space admins in the "Space settings" page, and the permissions for each space in "Wiki configuration" > "Manage space".

3 How can I change the position and order of pages?

When releasing a page, you can select the page position in the page tree. You can move this page again by clicking "Move" in … in the middle navigation bar.

You can also drag to change the order and position of multiple pages by clicking "Change page tree" beside the page tree in the left bar.

4 Can I revert to a previous page version?

All the historical page versions are saved. You can revert to a previous version in "Page History" in … in the middle navigation bar.

5 Other questions

Click the “?& rdquo; button in the top bar to view the documentation or contact support.
